criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Cis-gender men who report having sex with men;

          -  Over 18 years of age;

          -  Type 1 HIV infected;

          -  Born in a country other than France and arrived in France at the age of 15 at the
             earliest;

          -  Followed in Ile-de-France for their HIV infection and having consulted at least once
             in the participating center during the last 12 months;

          -  Non-opposition to the collection of their health data, after being well informed of
             the study and the patient rights in accordance with RGPD and LIL (French regulation)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Somatic or psychiatric pathology making it impossible to participate in an
             investigation;

          -  Communication disorder making it impossible to read (or oral responses in the event of
             assisted questionnaire completion).
